WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Making business phone calls in English can feel intimidating - you can't see facial expressions or body language. But with the right phrases and practice, you'll feel confident on any professional call. Today, you'll master essential phone call skills.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:30.000
In this lesson, we'll cover four essential phone call scenarios:

First, answering business calls professionally.
Second, making outgoing calls with clear introductions.
Third, transferring calls and taking messages.
And fourth, ending calls politely and effectively.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:40.000
These skills are crucial for customer service, client communication, and daily business operations.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Let's start with answering business calls. The first 10 seconds set the tone.

**Professional Greetings**:
'[Company Name], this is [Your Name]. How can I help you?'
'Good morning, [Company Name], [Your Name] speaking. How may I assist you?'

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:15.000
'[Company Name], [Your Name]. What can I do for you?'

Notice three key elements: Company name, your name, and offer to help.

**Slightly More Formal**:
'Hello, this is [Your Name] from [Company Name]. How can I help you today?'

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:30.000
Practice these greetings - they sound professional and confident.

